                         Instructor Refresher Forum
                                 (MIT-311D)
              Increasing Training Effectiveness Who, What, How?
                         Friday, September 21, 2001
                            Pacific: 9 AM - 1 PM
                           Mountain: 10 AM - 2 PM
                            Central: 11 AM - 3 PM
                           Eastern: 12 noon - 4 PM

   Method of delivery: Interactive television broadcast

   Duration: 4-hour*

   To Register:
   To register for this course, please contact your site training point of
   contact. If you do not know who your site point of contact, please call
   Customer Service at (505) 845-5170 X310.

   Please register now.

     * The final deadline for registering is Friday, September 7.

                               Prerequisites:
    Basic Instructor Training (MIT-111) is recommended but not required.

                           Questions on Content?:
        E-mail Margy Niemack, lead instructor: mniemack@nnsi.doe.gov
                            mniemack@nnsi.doe.gov

                                 *Logistics:
             Two 10-minute breaks; OK to bring a snack or lunch

   Who can Participate?
   This four-hour seminar is designed for all government training
   professionals including instructors, instructional designers, training
   managers, adjuncts, and training specialists. The satellite broadcast
   is free to DOE personnel and contractors, and is available to
   participants from other government agencies for a nominal fee.

   For other federal agencies: $138.58 per participant.

   To register for this course, please contact your site training point of
   contact. If you do not know who your site point of contact is, please
   call Customer Service at (505) 845-5170 X310. (Note: If you have
   colleagues at another agency, who may not receive this notice, call
   Angela Chavez in Registration and we'll get information to them.)

   What content will these presentations cover?
   "What skill are we training?" - Bloom's Taxonomy

   Case Study (OJT) -"Winning the Inspection Game"

   Case Study (Classroom) - "Walking the Talk"

   Learning Theory - Student-led vs. Instructor-led Activities

   Case Study (Force-on-Force) - "Winning the Performance Game"

   Case Study (Counterintelligence Training) - "Doing What Works!"
   Student-led Activities

   Who are the presenters?
   Margy Niemack---NNSI/Central Training Academy
   Dr. Jim Olsen Jr.-NNSI/Central Training Academy
   David Dailey-NNSI/Central Training Academy
   Bill Risley & Ben Huff-Los Alamos National Laboratory
   Willie Edwards-NNSI/Counterintelligence Training Academy






